Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Thinly slice the @tomato{1}(thinly sliced).

> TIP: To avoid turning on your oven, toast the bagels in the toaster instead.

Halve the @bagels{2} (1 per person, you can save the rest for use later).

Toast in your #toaster{}.

Once toasted, pop the bagels onto plates and spread @mustard{1%sachet} over the cut side of each half.

> TIP: Alternatively, toast the bagels in the oven for 4-6 mins.

Pull the @sliced Irish ham{80%grams} apart into large pieces and layer on top of the mustard.

Top with the tomato slices and @grated cheese{50%grams}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Enjoy your bagels either open-faced or sandwiched closed—it's up to you!